stories.text:
Due to circumstances outside of my control I have to stretch the current $500 I have for the next 38 years. I live in a pretty cheap country and don't pay rent. This is about $0.03 per day, it seems like it should be able to be good for a few grains of rice or beans.

I am not looking for investment advice or get-rich-quick advice, I am looking for advice on how I can make what I have last for 38 years. I can't get any further income. For example should I try to grow some beans on my windowsill?
